==English==

===Verb===
'''Winded'''
# To cause a person to lose their breath
#:''The boxer was '''winded''' when his opponent hit his solar plexus.''

===Derived Expresion===
'''long winded'''
# Talking excessively
#:''The professor's '''long winded''' description of ancient hieroglyphs left the students somnolent.''

===Adjective===
'''winded'''
# The state of being short of breath
#:''She was '''winded''' from her long run.''